    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-10T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="808"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d808">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/255: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-10T20:00:00+03:00"
                            >April 10, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>251. British Ambassador<note n="22" xml:id="d808fn22">Sir Hughe M.
                        Knatchbull-Hugessen.</note> informed me today that in connection with
                    furnishing of supplies to Turkey he had received instructions from his
                    Government that this subject would be dealt with in Ankara, with the exception
                    that requirements which British authorities do not undertake to supply from the
                    United Kingdom will be considered by the United States authorities in
                    Washington, if necessary, with the British or Turkish Embassies.</p>
                <pb facs="0705" n="693" xml:id="pg_693"/>
                <p>The Ambassador’s instructions further provided that he is to endeavor to induce
                    Turkish Government to accept this procedure.</p>
                <p>He requested me to advise him if and when I receive instructions to like
                    effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
